A new report by has ranked Kilimani, Westlands and Thindigua as among the best areas for apartment development in Nairobi even as more and more Kenyans seek out affordable housing within and around the capital, with the market still largely ignoring the lower end of the market. The report by Cytonn real estate analyzes the current state of the residential real estate sector in Kenya in terms of supply, demand, drivers, challenges, and performance. 